comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T12:25:47.265Z",codex-root,"text=Duplicate check: searched all pm statuses for PM-CLI-2E, readFileIfExists EISDIR settings, and settings.json directory. No canonical item covers this bootstrap failure. Fresh Sentry event 31835fc7f0cb4db789e12191560cf5b9 occurred once at 2026-07-21T11:37:08Z in readFileIfExists/readSettingsWithMetadata during malformed-settings acceptance."
  "2026-07-21T12:54:33.832Z",codex-root,"Evidence: TDD reproduced EISDIR and now proves cached fallback plus recovery; linked search/background tests pass 72/72 and settings tests pass 31/31. Manual acceptance in /tmp/pm-cli-settings-acceptance.oDxVsG completed without a stack trace, emitted settings_read_invalid_json remediation, finished health, and recorded a successful telemetry flush at 2026-07-21T12:29:01.173Z. Full repository verification passes 332 files/6,059 tests at exact 100/100/100/100, plus static quality, 100% docstrings, zero duplication, package boundary, token budget, and secret scanning. Sentry PM-CLI-2E remains intentionally unresolved until merged-commit proof."
  "2026-07-21T13:02:23.648Z",codex-root,"Pre-push Greptile review 96db75c8-0660-4671-9d3b-f447434636fc rated the diff 4/5 and safe to merge, with two P2 improvements: separate filesystem-read failures from invalid JSON for actionable telemetry, and make success-with-warning search/background behavior explicit in the focused mock contract. Reopened only this actively edited item to implement both before push."
  "2026-07-21T13:07:29.473Z",codex-root,"Greptile follow-up evidence: both P2 observations addressed. Filesystem failures now use settings_read_fs_error while invalid JSON retains settings_read_invalid_json; remediation maps to pm config list --json; focused warning-return tests assert exact mutation/background propagation. Manual temp health output shows no crash, warning provenance, and remediation_map. Full verification passes 332 files/6,060 tests at exact 100/100/100/100 plus static quality, 100% docstrings, zero duplication, package boundary, token budget, and secret scanning."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T12:54:34.487Z",codex-root,"Operational contract: an unreadable settings path must preserve diagnostic availability while search refresh refuses to run with fallback defaults; otherwise a resilience fix can silently change semantic indexing behavior."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T12:54:35.086Z",codex-root,"Fallback settings need provenance, not just values. Consumers that perform external or background work must inspect settings-read warnings so safe CLI recovery does not become unsafe default-driven execution."
